=== Noun ===
'''advocate''' (''plural'' '''advocates''')
# (''countable'') A person who argues the case of another person, (for example a "[[lawyer]]" in a [[court]]).
#:''The lawyer was one of a few good child '''advocates''' in town.''
# (''countable'') A person who speaks in support of a plan or project, etc.
#:''She has been a strong '''advocate''' for reform.''

